601
00:34:30.660 --> 00:34:34.560
All right. So good afternoon. I'm Adam Blaisdell, physician scientist at UCSF.

602
00:34:34.660 --> 00:34:38.040
Today I'll talk about the under-recognized problem of perforin

603
00:34:38.060 --> 00:34:41.380
degranulation in CD8 tumor infiltrating lymphocytes, or TILs,

604
00:34:42.580 --> 00:34:44.761
and I'll show that A20 sits at the heart of this problem.

605
00:34:46.341 --> 00:34:47.440
I have no disclosures.

606
00:34:48.960 --> 00:34:51.140
My talk today covers three major themes.

607
00:34:51.560 --> 00:34:55.120
First, I'll show you how targeting A20 improves

608
00:34:55.160 --> 00:34:57.340
adaptive cellular therapies, or ACTs.

609
00:34:58.780 --> 00:35:02.540
Second, I'll discuss why A20 is an intriguing target with respect to

610
00:35:02.580 --> 00:35:03.000
