728
00:42:06.500 --> 00:42:07.040
RIP3.

729
00:42:08.780 --> 00:42:10.260
RIP3 canonically

730
00:42:11.200 --> 00:42:14.340
triggers necroptosis and cell death via MLKL,

731
00:42:15.220 --> 00:42:16.760
and this is suppressed by A20.

732
00:42:18.620 --> 00:42:22.440
Non-canonical RIP3 signaling is less well defined but

733
00:42:22.480 --> 00:42:24.860
can involve the inflammasome and caspase-1.

734
00:42:26.140 --> 00:42:29.300
This biology has primarily been described in myeloid cells.

735
00:42:30.340 --> 00:42:32.180
Little is known about whether it operates in T

736
00:42:32.280 --> 00:42:36.080
cellsNevertheless, in published

737
00:42:36.200 --> 00:42:39.580
single cell transcriptomic data sets, we found MC38

738
00:42:39.620 --> 00:42:41.480
Ttex and human Ttex

739
00:42:42.980 --> 00:42:45.540
upregulated genes in this non-canonical pathway.

740
00:42:49.120 --> 00:42:52.520
And remarkably, RIP3 ablation nearly

741
