762
00:44:14.740 --> 00:44:18.380
To summarize, targeting A20 or zinc finger seven via

763
00:44:18.440 --> 00:44:22.350
Cas9 or base editing in ACTs greatly enhanced their efficacy.

764
00:44:24.620 --> 00:44:28.240
Zinc finger seven differentially regulates cytokine versus perforin effector

765
00:44:28.280 --> 00:44:31.800
mechanisms, one at the level of transcription, one at degranulation.

766
00:44:33.940 --> 00:44:37.720
And targeting zinc finger seven unlocks a non-canonical RIP3 caspase-1

767
00:44:37.840 --> 00:44:40.720
axis that regulates perforin but not cytokine release.

768
00:44:41.680 --> 00:44:45.380
We aim to further map the upstream and downstream signals in this axis, and we'll

769
00:44:45.400 --> 00:44:48.940
try to exploit this pathway to enhance ACTs.

770
00:44:50.940 --> 00:44:53.960
And finally, I want to acknowledge this amazing collaborative effort with

771
00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:57.040
substantial contributions across three labs at UCSF.

772
00:44:57.380 --> 00:44:58.380
Thank you for your attention.

773
00:45:09.900 --> 00:45:11.840
Hi. Zaya Gill from Penn. That was really nice work.

774
00:45:13.700 --> 00:45:16.920
So the increased degranulation,

775
00:45:18.100 --> 00:45:22.040
better killing, but also within those effector cells or the

776
00:45:22.100 --> 00:45:25.720
Ttex, at least, you're seeing evidence of activation of

777
00:45:26.340 --> 00:45:29.660
non-canonical RIPK3 signaling. And so

