00:45:37.700 --> 00:45:37.940
Yeah.

781
00:45:38.760 --> 00:45:42.660
We don't see an obvious cell death signal with the usual apoptosis

782
00:45:42.700 --> 00:45:45.460
stains or the cell impermeable dyes.

783
00:45:46.900 --> 00:45:47.240
So

784
00:45:48.840 --> 00:45:49.880
we don't fully know

785
00:45:51.680 --> 00:45:52.300
why it's

786
00:45:53.200 --> 00:45:56.820
outside the world of cell death, per se, because obviously that would be a bad

787
00:45:56.860 --> 00:45:58.660
thing for the T cells, you would think.

788
00:46:00.180 --> 00:46:01.460
So we think it's

789
00:46:03.740 --> 00:46:07.140
connected to possibly stress activation

790
00:46:07.180 --> 00:46:10.400
pathways that, in the absence of A20, turn out to be

